title: Merge Intervals
description: Given an array of intervals where intervals[i] = [starti, endi], merge all overlapping intervals, and return an array of the non-overlapping intervals that cover all the intervals in the input.
input_format: The first line may contain the number of intervals (optional, parsing logic handles it). The subsequent lines effectively describe the intervals. Input format for judge: list of space-separated integers, taken as pairs. e.g. '1 3 2 6 8 10 15 18' represents brackets [1,3], [2,6], [8,10], [15,18].
output_format: Print the merged intervals, one per line (e.g. '1 6').
